        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 4:28PM EDT by NWS Northern Indiana</headline>
        <description>At 428 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Addison, or 10 miles northeast of Hillsdale, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Hillsdale, Jonesville, Jerome, Somerset, Moscow, North Adams, Osseo,
and Somerset Center.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
